Running the Carbon Footprint Calculator (Command Line Guide)

This guide explains how to compile and run the CarbonScope Java Swing application using the command line

- Before running the program, ensure our .java files are stored in the same folder

- Your IDE should be navigated to our project folder (Project-CarbonScope)

- Compile the program using:
javac CarbonScope.java

- Run the program, using the main class:
java CarbonScope


TROUBLESHOOTING
Error: Could not find or load main class

Cause: Running Java from the wrong folder

Please ensure the files are in the same directory!
